'''The Bergen Corpus of London Teenage Language (COLT)''' is a data set of samples of [[English language|spoken English]] that was compiled in 1993 from tape recorded and transcribed conversations by teens between the ages of 13 and 17 in London schools.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://clu.uni.no/icame/colt/cd/SUMMARY.PDF|title = COLT Summary|date = |accessdate = March 29, 2015|website = |publisher = }}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|title = English Adjective Comparison: A Historical Perspective|last = González-Díaz|first = Victorina|publisher = John Benjamins|year = 2008|isbn = |location = |pages = 9}}</ref> This corpus, which has been tagged for [[part of speech]] using the CLAWS 6 tagset, is one of the linguistic research projects housed at the [[University of Bergen]] in Norway<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://clu.uni.no/icame/colt/|title = COLT: The Bergen Corpus of London Teenage Talk|date = November 20, 2003|accessdate = March 29, 2015|website = |publisher = }}</ref>'''''.  '''''Linguistic analysis based on this corpus material has appeared in the book ''Trends in Teenage Talk<ref>{{Cite book|title = Trends in Teenage Talk|last = Stenström|first = Anna-Brita|publisher = John Benjamins|authorlink1=Anna-Brita Stenström|year = 2002|isbn = |location = |pages = |display-authors=etal}}</ref>'' and later journal articles.<ref>{{Cite journal|url = http://www.spertus.es/publications/ignacio/2011palaciosmartinezatlantis.pdf|title = The Language of British Teenagers. A Preliminary Study of its Main Grammatical Features|last = Palacios Martínez|first = Ignacio M.|date = 2011|journal = Journal of the Spanish Association of Anglo-American Studies|doi = |pmid = |access-date = March 29, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title = The Expression of Negation in British Teenagers’ Language: A Preliminary Study|last = Palacios Martinez|first = Ignacio|date = 2010|journal = Journal of English Linguistics|doi = |pmid = }}</ref>

